1 (b) The Deaf Culture Digital Library shall:
2 (1) Conduct a needs assessment to identify gaps in library services for deaf
3 patrons and to implement strategies to fill the gaps and better coordinate library services
4 for the deaf;
5 (2) In coordination with the Governor’s Office of the Deaf and Hard of
6 Hearing, develop and provide sensitivity training for State and county library staff to help
7 them better understand deaf patrons and their needs;
8 (3) Develop a website that will allow for information sharing and
9 coordination between the Deaf Culture Digital Library and county library systems;
10 (4) In coordination with the State Library Agency, develop deaf–related
11 programs and materials and share them with county library systems and other libraries in
12 the State;
13 (5) Develop partnerships and strategic alliances with other entities,
14 including:
15 (i) The Governor’s Office of the Deaf and Hard of Hearing;
16 (ii) County library systems;
17 (iii) The State Library Agency;
18 (iv) Veterans’ groups;
19 (v) State and local arts councils;
20 (vi) Senior citizens organizations; and
21 (vii) Deaf and hard of hearing organizations, including:
22 1. The National Association of the Deaf;
23 2. The Hearing Loss Association of America; and
24 3. The Maryland Association of the Deaf;
25 (6) Encourage partnerships and collaborations with information service
26 providers to help provide virtual access to information and research;
27 (7) Form a Deaf Culture Digital Library Advisory Board to provide advice
28 on initiatives that further advance the mission and goals of the Deaf Culture Digital

