1 Library and the majority of whose members are deaf or hard of hearing and selected from
2 the following entities:
3 (i) County library systems;
4 (ii) The State Library Agency;
5 (iii) The Governor’s Office of the Deaf and Hard of Hearing;
6 (iv) Statewide deaf and hard of hearing organizations; and
7 (v) Other organizations as agreed on by the Governor’s Office of the
8 Deaf and Hard of Hearing and the State Library Agency; and
9 (8) Establish a Deaf Culture Digital Library “Friends of the Library” group
10 composed of individuals who are strongly committed, well–positioned, and able to promote
11 community involvement, advocacy, and funding for the Deaf Culture Digital Library.
12 (c) The lead employee or coordinator who manages the Deaf Culture Digital
13 Library shall be:
14 (1) A deaf or hard of hearing individual; and
15 (2) Knowledgeable and experienced concerning issues affecting deaf and
16 hard of hearing individuals.
17 (D) FOR FISCAL YEAR 2026 AND EACH FISCAL YEAR THEREAFTER, THE
18 GOVERNOR SHALL INCLUDE IN THE ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION OF
19 $450,000 TO THE DEAF CULTURE DIGITAL LIBRARY.
20 (E) THE DEAF CULTURE DIGITAL LIBRARY SHALL SUBMIT ITS ANNUAL
21 OPERATING BUDGET TO THE STATE LIBRARY AGENCY ON OR BEFORE JUNE 1 EACH
22 YEAR.
23 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
24 1, 2025.

